D.5 Image Analysis Protocol

1. Calibration: Use scale marker to convert pixels to mm.
2. Node displacement measurement: For each grid node (i,j), calculate displacement vector dᵢⱼ = (xᵢⱼ(ΔP) − xᵢⱼ(baseline), yᵢⱼ(ΔP) − yᵢⱼ(baseline)).
3. Strain calculation: Engineering strain ε = ΔL / L₀ for each grid cell.
4. Principal strain: Compute eigenvalues of strain tensor to identify maximum and minimum principal strain directions.
5. Pattern distortion index (PDI): PDI = (1 / N) Σ|dᵢⱼ| / L_cell, where L_cell = nominal cell width (5 mm).

