ΔP (kPa) PDI Interpretation
101.3 (ambient) 0.00 Baseline
60 0.02–0.05 Elastic deformation, recoverable
30 0.05–0.10 Moderate distortion
10 0.10–0.20 Significant distortion, warning threshold
5 0.20–0.30 High distortion, replace seam
0.6 (Mars surface) 0.30–0.50 Critical, immediate replacement indicated

D.7 Calibration Curve: Strain Gauge Function

Measure PDI as function of ΔP, fit polynomial:

PDI(ΔP) = a × (ΔP)² + b × (ΔP) + c

Inverse function gives estimated ΔP from observed PDI:

ΔP_est = f⁻¹(PDI)

This transforms pattern distortion into a visual strain gauge — an indexical sign of structural stress.

